General Topic

Impressive Password Statistics

to know
Credentials are one of the most sought after and frequently exchanged digital goods in the darknet economy. Many people are still making common password mistakes, such as using their favorite year or using highly popular (and crackable) strings of characters.

A recent study shows that :

  • 50% of people use the same password for all their logins
  • 51% of people have the same password for their work and personal accounts
  • Over 80% of data breaches are due to poor password security.
  • Only 31.3% of internet users update their passwords twice a year

News Impersonation cybercrimes are on a rise

Fraudsters targeted the Dubai-based billionaire Rizwan Sajan, founder and chairman of Danube Group, by impersonating him and requesting funds from his acquaintances and followers.

We are observing a rise in the number of impersonation attacks at ADX, and fraudsters are attempting to impersonate our key officials such as the CEO, CFO and others. Maintain a watchful eye over the emails that you receive, and report any communications that appear to be suspicious to the ADX Security Operations Center ( SOC@adx.ae ) .

LetMeSpy permanently shuts down after data breach
LetMeSpy has formally announced the closure of the company, as it cannot recover from the data breach in June earlier this year. Letmespy's administrators realized on 22 June that a data breach had occurred and notified the Polish Office for Personal Data Protection and filed complaint with law enforcement authorities. Initial digital forensics investigations revealed that hackers not only stole but also deleted personal and sensitive data.
Know more
MOVEit body count closes in on 400 orgs, 20M+ individuals
The MOVEit file transfer hack, a massive supply chain attack, has affected a growing number of victims and is considered one of the most significant hacks in recent years. As of July 19, around 383 organizations and over 20 million individuals have been compromised. Notable victims include the US Department of Energy, Shell, Deutsche Bank, EY, PwC, and TJX Companies. ADX data weren’t impacted with this breach.
Know more
Norway government ministries uncovered a data attack

The ministries' security and service organization has uncovered a data attack on the ICT platform of 12 ministries. Hackers exploited a zero-day vulnerability in third-party software. The attack affected the ministries' email systems, file servers, and websites.

The hackers also stole sensitive data, including email correspondence, financial information, and intellectual property.

Know more
Alpha data significant data breach

Alpha Data, a prominent IT service provider in UAE announced that they experienced a breach on 15 June. The breach exposed customer records, financial data, and internal documents of numerous organizations.

 

ADX data weren’t impacted with this breach.

 

Alpha data is an ADX-approved vendor that has been offering its services to the exchange. After conducting an investigation, we have come to the conclusion that this breach did not result in the exposure of any critical ADX data.

Multichain Pauses Operations After USD120 Million Cyber Heist
Blockchain bridge Multichain was hacked on July 6, 2023, and lost up to USD120 million. The hackers were able to exploit a vulnerability in the protocol to steal tokens from the Fantom, Dogechain, and Moonriver blockchains.
Know more
Brunswick Corporation lost $85 million in cyberattack
Brunswick Corporation, a significant marine industry player, incurred an $85 million expense due to a cyberattack. The incident disrupted their operations and affected systems and facilities.
